1\. Steps of Elive os Installation in VMware Workstation Player 

When I starte this part of the project, I isn’t sure if it would be complicated or straightforwardturnsout it was most smooth with a few small issues along the way. Here's howI installedEliveOSinavirtual machine using VMware Workstation Player 

1.1 VMware workstation Set-up process for Elive os 

The installation process is done using VMware workstation workstation free and open-sourcevirtalization tool. 

**Step 1:** I went to the official Elive OS webste and downloading the latest .iso file. The downloadwasaround 3.5 GB and took about 15-45 minutes with my internet connection.

![][image1]

**Step 2:** After opened VMware Workstation Player, I clicked on “Create a NewVirtual Machine.”![][image2]

For the installer option, I selecte: 

“Installer disc image file (iso)”, then browsed and selecte the Elive .iso I had downloaded.

![][image3]

Click Next. 

Note: If VMware says “Cannot detect operating system,” no worries—just continue manuallyselectingLinux. Because you can setetting up latter 

**Step 3**: VMware didn’t automatically detect the OS, so I manually selected: 

Guest OS: Linux 

Version: Ubuntu 64-bit. 

![][image4]

Click Next. 

**Step 4:** Name Your VM & Set Location for your new virtual environment 

I named the VM: 

Elive\_OS\_Abraham 

And saved it to a folder I created on my desktop for the project.

![][image5]

Click Next. 

**Step 5:** I set the virtual disk to: 

Disk size: 20 GB or more 

Store as a single file for better performance and display capacity ![][image6]

Click Next. 

**Step 6:** Customize Hardware (Optional but Recommended) 

Before finishing, I clicked on “Customize Hardware” and made a few changes: Memory: 2 GB 

Processors: 2 cores

Network Adapter: NAT (default) is fine for nework configuration 

Display: Enable 3D acceleration if desired 

![][image7]Click Close, then Finish. 

**Step 7:** Start the VM 

 I clicked “Play virtual machine”, and after a few seconds, the Elive OS live sessionloaded. 

I used the live environment to explore a bit, then clicked on the Elive Installer icon on the desktop to begin the actual installation. 

![][image8]It should boot into Elive’s Live environment or installer.

1.2 Elive Linux installation process 

Once you're on the Elive desktop installer: 

![][image9]

**Step 1:** Start the Installer 

Click on the Elive Installer icon as shown in the above image 

Step 2: Language and Keyboard 

Choose your language

![][image10]  
Select your keyboard layout 

Click Next 

**Step 3:** Partitioning 

Choose Automatic Partitioning (recommended for most users) It will automatically set up root and swap partitions 

![][image11]

Alternatively If you're experienced you can choose manual partitioning

Confirm to continue and wait untile the disk is installed the OS

**Step 4:** configuire the installed Elive os   
follow some steps to complete configuration 

![][image12]

Network configuration 

![][image13]

**Step 5:** User and System Settings 

Set your username, password, and hostname (computer name)

![][image14]Confirm the password and continue 

**Step 6:** complete Installation 

Confirm all your choices 

![][image15]

After Installation 

After that, I was asked to reboot the system. Before restarting, I made sure to disconnect the ISO file from the virtual CD drive (in VMware settings), so it wouldn't boot into the installer again.

![][image16]

First Boot into Installed Elive 

Once it restarted, Elive loaded properly\! I logged in with my user credentials and began exploring the system. 

![][image17]

Now we can you use the new operating system like these example chrome.
